App State Design (Central Store)


| State Name      | Type                | Purpose                                                                                     |
| --------------- | ------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| document        | ExtractedDoc / None | Stores the currently loaded PDF document including extracted text, page count, and OCR flag |
| document_hash   | str / None          | Stores SHA256 hash of the uploaded PDF to detect if the same file is re-uploaded            |
| chat_history    | list of dict        | Stores the full chat conversation as a list of messages (each message has role and content) |
| is_loading      | bool                | Indicates whether the app is currently processing (PDF extraction or LLM response)          |
| error_message   | str / None          | Stores any error message from PDF extraction or LLM call to display in UI                   |
| pdf_metadata    | dict                | Stores derived PDF info such as page count, extraction method, character count              |
| is_truncated    | bool                | Indicates whether PDF text was truncated due to context size limits                         |
| input_text      | str                 | Stores the current user input in the chat input box                                         |
| has_document    | bool                | Indicates whether a valid PDF is currently loaded                                           |
| last_user_query | str / None          | Stores the last question asked by the user (useful for debugging or retry)                  |                                                                              |
| --------------- | ------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |


Notes:

* chat_history format:
  [
  {"role": "user", "content": "..."},
  {"role": "assistant", "content": "..."}
  ]

* document is the core state used by chat_controller and document_controller

* pdf_metadata is derived from document but stored separately for easy UI binding

* has_document is a convenience flag to simplify UI logic (enable/disable input)

* is_loading can be used later for spinners or disabled UI even in synchronous version
